replies.body:
{{champion:161}} and {{champion:268}} just so happen to have "laser" type autoattacks as opposed to the projectile based autoattacks of all other ranged champions. They aren't blocked by windwall and have no travel time which makes it much easier to time last hits.

I believe AA's are a part of balance. {{champion:30}} {{champion:69}} have low-cooldown abilities that they usually use to last hit instead. They want {{champion:34}} to have a hard time cs-ing levels 1-5 as a way to give opponents a window of opportunity to zone her before she hits 6 and inevitably takes control of the lane. {{champion:429}}'s AA animation was much shorter on release, they increased it drastically so you actually have a chance to hit her before she starts hopping. Old {{champion:78}} had an atrocious AA frame and they intentionally left it clunky for fear that any change could break her.

And then we have possibly the worst AA animation in the game {{champion:254}}
